column5: Well, a lazy Sunday casting bucktails paid off.  We saw 7, hooked 4 and I landed this 44 " Kawartha's beauty...and this was my first time musky fishing.  I now know why this is so addictive.  I'm hooked!
Great fish!  What do you figure on the weight of that one?

It was thick (check out that head...not Mike's head, the musky's) so we were guessing somewhere between 22 - 25 lbs.  She is big but if the one that took that bite out of her tail is still swimming around watch out!
Nice kawartha ski!  Congrats.  You don't it yet but you are about to have a lot less disposable cash.  Once the muskie bug hits you will wonder how you just dropped $400 on lures.
Nice first Muskie I am still trying to get one 44 inches only in my dreams.MTP
Nice job beauty fish.
Nice job....  your in it now....
Awesome first outing!  Congrats  Whopper
Way to go! Amazing beauty!  Easton
Yup, a fine looking Kawartha specimen. Congrats!
very nice, thanks for sharing.
What a beaut!! Congrats. For a first outing those are fine results to say the least.  Cheers, 1leg
Great looking fish, congrats.
Beauty fish, congrats on you first muskie.
Awesome, great fish.
awsome.   which lake did u exactly go and what did u use?
Nice fish, can you imagine how much harder it would have pulled if it had a whole tail? Congrats!
That is a nice Kawartha Muskie!  Awesome horizontal hold and release shot!
Congrats....  Great looking fish
Thats real beauty...
beautiful looking fish, congrats on your catch
